<TITLE> BDR sieze 50,000 Yaba tablets in Comilla </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Comilla, Feb 6 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh Rifles seized 50,000 Yaba tablets in Comilla on Saturday. BDR officials said the haul of the illegal narcotic was worth at least Tk 40 million. Sergeant Abu Taher of 33 Rifles Battalion told reporters the made the seizure as they were patrolling the Zalua Para area of the Sadar upazila early morning. "We saw a man carrying a carton that made us suspicious. He ran off dropping the box when we ordered him to stop." Around 50,000 Yaba tablets were found in 50 cases inside the larger carton. The seized tablets are being held at the 33 Rifles Battalion headquarters. The supply and use of Yaba, a relatively cheap but powerful stimulant, has increased dramatically in recent years. Law enforcement agencies say they have made several seizures of the drug in different areas of the country over the past few days. bdnew
